    • Uses of BlockFace in org.bukkit.block

      Methods in org.bukkit.block that return BlockFace 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      BlockFace Block.getFace(Block block)
      Gets the face relation of this block compared to the given block

      For example: Block current = world.getBlockAt(100, 100, 100); Block target = world.getBlockAt(100, 101, 100); current.getFace(target) == BlockFace.Up;
      If the given block is not connected to this block, null may be returned
      BlockFace BlockFace.getOppositeFace()

      Returns an array containing the constants of this enum type, in the order they are declared.
